excerpt: A short trek leads visitors to this small waterfall situated in a lush, jungle environment.
detail_description: Nestled in a vibrant jungle setting, Kathu Waterfall is a hidden gem that promises an adventure for all ages. A short trek from the road leads you to this charming spot, conveniently located near Phuket Wake Park. While the base may seem unassuming, with a local eatery serving delicious made-to-order meals, the true beauty lies above. To reach the top of Kathu Waterfall, prepare for an exhilarating climb involving steep stairs and slippery rocks.
name: Kathu Waterfall
address: W8MF+Q5C, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Tourist attraction featuring up-close interaction with tigers in caged enclosures.
detail_description: Tiger Kingdom in Phuket offers a unique and unforgettable experience for visitors to get up close and personal with tigers in safe, caged enclosures. The attraction provides an opportunity to learn about these majestic animals, take a leisurely walk through the park, and even feed or take photos with the tigers. With premium insurance included in the ticket, visitors can also explore educational exhibits and enjoy a personal encounter with the tigers.
name: Tiger Kingdom - Phuket
address: 118/88 Moo 7, Kathu, Phuket, Thailand

excerpt: Stretching from inland jungle hills to busy coastal resorts, Kathu District contains Patong Beach, where high-energy bars and discos line nightlife strip Bangla Road and visitors buy brand-name surfwear. Quieter Freedom Beach draws visitors for snorkeling and seafront dining. Families swim and picnic around gentle forest cascades at Kathu Waterfall and watch elaborate Thai-themed shows at FantaSea park.
detail_description: Kathu District, part of Phuket, is a diverse area that includes popular beaches like Patong and Kamala. While Patong Beach offers vibrant nightlife and shopping opportunities, Freedom Beach provides a quieter escape for snorkeling and dining by the sea. The district also features natural attractions such as Kathu Waterfall and entertainment options like FantaSea park.
name: Kathu
address: Kathu District, Phuket, Thailand

detail_description: Suwan Khiri Wong Temple, also known as Wat Patong, offers a serene escape from the bustling development and lively nightlife of Patong. This Theravada temple serves as a significant hub for local Thai Buddhism and boasts an array of stunning structures such as the main ubosot, pagoda, monastery hall, and various Buddha statues. Despite its challenging location at a busy Y intersection, this often overlooked gem showcases remarkable architecture and provides a peaceful atmosphere for visitors to explore.
name: Wat Suwankeereewong
address: W826+W5X, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Lively Phuket Old Town is known for brightly painted, century-old Sino-Portuguese townhouses, with a well-preserved row along Soi Rommanee. Main street Thalang Road has stores selling artisanal ice cream and batik fabrics and a Sunday market for souvenirs and street food like fried banana. The Thai Hua Museum features exhibits on Chinese immigrant culture, and Jui Tui Shrine displays colorful statues of Chinese gods.
detail_description: Old Phuket Town is a vibrant area known for its well-preserved Sino-Portuguese townhouses, artisanal shops, and colorful markets. Visitors can explore the Thai Hua Museum and Jui Tui Shrine to learn about Chinese immigrant culture and see colorful statues of Chinese gods.
name: Old Phuket Town
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Andamanda Phuket, set to open in early 2022, is poised to become the largest leisure and family entertainment destination on the island. Spanning 9 hectares, it will showcase Thai culture and heritage. Meanwhile, Karon Viewpoint offers breathtaking panoramic views of Kata Noi Beach, Kata Bay with its iconic island, and Karon Beach. The attraction features a variety of slides suitable for both kids and adults, offering options from gentle to thrilling experiences.
name: Andamanda Phuket
address: 333, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Lively road with a vibrant nighttime scene of bars, clubs, market stalls & street performers.
detail_description: Bangla Road is the pulsating heart of nightlife in Patong, Phuket, where excitement and energy collide. This lively thoroughfare is lined with an array of bars, clubs, and market stalls that come alive after dark. As you stroll down Bangla Road, you'll encounter a vibrant mix of Go-Go bars and pubs filled with friendly locals and travelers alike. The atmosphere is electric, inviting you to dance the night away or simply enjoy a drink while soaking in the sights and sounds around you.
name: Bangla Rd
address: Tambon Patong, Amphoe Kathu, Chang Wat Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Large temple complex from the early 19th century, with Buddha paintings, golden statues & gardens.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Phuket, Chaithararam Temple, also known as Wat Chalong, is a stunning temple complex that dates back to the early 19th century. This sacred site is adorned with intricate Buddha paintings and shimmering golden statues, surrounded by beautifully landscaped gardens that invite tranquility. The temple holds significant historical importance for the local community, particularly due to its association with Luangpho Chaem—a revered monk known for his mastery in meditation and traditional medicine.
name: Wat Chalong
address: 70 หมู่ที่ 6 Chao Fah Tawan Tok Rd, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Elaborate mall with many specialty shops & casual eateries, plus a movie theater & trampoline park.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Patong Beach, Jungceylon is a sprawling shopping paradise that promises an unforgettable experience for every visitor. This expansive mall features a diverse array of specialty shops and casual dining options, making it the perfect spot to unwind after a day in the sun. From trendy clothing and stylish accessories to unique souvenirs and spa products, Jungceylon has something for everyone.
name: Jungceylon
address: 175,177,181,193,195,197, 201 ถนน ราษฎร์อุทิศ, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Forested hilltop home to roaming monkeys, with an observation platform offering panoramic views.
detail_description: Monkey Hill Viewpoint, also known as Toh Sae Hill, is a forested hilltop in Phuket Old Town that offers panoramic views of the city. Visitors can purchase seeds and nuts to feed the roaming monkeys and enjoy the stunning sights from the observation platform. It's best to visit in the early morning or evening to avoid strong sun, and be cautious with belongings around the friendly macaques. The hill also features a shrine popular for seeking lucky lottery numbers.
name: Monkey Hill Viewpoint
address: Ratsada, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Compact zoo featuring live crocodile, elephant & monkey performances.
detail_description: Phuket Zoo is a popular destination for families looking to provide their children with exciting and educational experiences. The zoo offers a variety of activities, including the chance to interact with animals, watch circus performances featuring elephants, monkeys, and crocodiles, feed the animals, and take photos with them. The compact 12-acre zoo is home to a diverse range of wildlife such as ostriches, peacocks, tigers, crocodiles, and elephants.
name: Phuket Zoo
address: 23 Soi Pa Lai 2, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Elephant Jungle Sanctuary Phuket is a must-visit destination for travelers of all ages. The sanctuary offers an unforgettable experience with these majestic creatures, allowing visitors to interact with them in a responsible and ethical manner. The guides are friendly, knowledgeable, and professional, ensuring that the visit is stress-free and enjoyable for everyone. Additionally, the transportation provided is comfortable and punctual, making it easy to access the sanctuary.
name: Elephant Jungle Sanctuary Phuket
address: 2, 12, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Large wakeboarding park with obstacle courses & lessons, plus other recreational activities.
detail_description: Phuket Wake Park is a paradise for wakeboarding enthusiasts, offering challenging obstacle courses and lessons for all skill levels. The park is known as the best wake park in Asia, providing professional coaching and training cables for beginners. In addition to wakeboarding, visitors can enjoy other recreational activities and fitness training options. After an exhilarating day on the water, guests can relax in comfortable lounges and savor delicious Thai cuisine.
name: Phuket Wake Park
address: 86 Vichitsongkram Rd, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: The 45m-tall marble Buddha statue on a mountaintop offers panoramic views, a cafe & gift shop.
detail_description: The Big Buddha, officially known as "Phraphutthamingmongkhol-akenagakhiri Buddha," stands majestically at 45 meters tall atop Nakerd Mountain in Phuket. This stunning white marble statue is not only a significant religious site but also offers breathtaking panoramic views of the island, including Phuket Town and Chalong Bay. The journey to this iconic landmark is made easy with well-paved roads, despite some winding curves.
name: The Big Buddha, Phuket
address: Karon, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

excerpt: Phuket City, on Phuket Island, is the capital of Thailand’s Phuket Province. In the Old Town, Thalang Road is lined with colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese buildings. Built in 1903 by a wealthy tin merchant, Baan Chinpracha mansion has Italian floor tiles, shuttered windows and antique furniture. Set in a 1930s manor, the Thai Hua Museum has exhibits on Phuket’s culture and history.
detail_description: Phuket, the vibrant capital of Thailand's Phuket Province, is a treasure trove of culture and history. Strolling through Old Town, you'll be captivated by the colorful 19th-century shophouses and Sino-Portuguese architecture that line Thalang Road. A visit to Baan Chinpracha mansion reveals its stunning Italian floor tiles and antique furnishings, while the Thai Hua Museum offers fascinating insights into local heritage within a charming 1930s manor.
name: Phuket
address: Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Relaxed, sandy bay beach & fishing village set amidst wooded hills with nearby accommodations.
detail_description: Nestled along the stunning western coast of Phuket Island, Kamala Beach is a serene and picturesque sandy bay that offers a delightful escape from the bustling tourist hotspots. This hidden gem stretches for 2 kilometers and is framed by lush wooded hills, creating an idyllic backdrop for relaxation.
name: Kamala Beach
address: Kamala, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Tours of a rum distillery, along with cocktail workshops & an open-air bar serving drinks & tapas.
detail_description: If you're looking to dive into the vibrant spirit of Phuket, The Distillery Phuket - Home of Chalong Bay is a must-visit destination. This award-winning rum distillery offers an immersive experience where you can witness the fascinating process of rum production, from sugarcane pressing to fermentation and distillation. Made entirely from 100% natural Thai sugarcane grown without harmful chemicals, Chalong Bay's artisan rum stands out for its purity and quality.
name: The Distillery Phuket - Home of Chalong Bay
address: 14, 2 Soi Palai, Chalong, Amphur Muang, Phuket 83130, Thailand

excerpt: Popular zipline attraction featuring multiple courses & sky bridges through jungle terrain.
detail_description: Flying Hanuman is an exhilarating zipline experience that takes you soaring through the lush jungles of Phuket, offering a unique perspective from 40 meters above ground. This adventure features multiple courses and sky bridges, allowing visitors to navigate the stunning hillsides while surrounded by nature's beauty. Before embarking on your thrilling journey, you'll receive important safety information in a cozy bamboo-and-thatch hut equipped with a flat-screen TV.
name: Flying Hanuman
address: 89/16, ซอย น้ำตกกระทู้, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Colorful 1911 Chinese shrine & the site of the annual Phuket Vegetarian Festival.
detail_description: Jui Tui Shrine, a vibrant Chinese shrine in Phuket, is known for its annual Vegetarian Festival. After undergoing renovations, the shrine now houses three large statues of different Chinese gods, with Tean Hu Huan Soy being the most prominent. The shrine's location was moved following a fire that nearly destroyed it years ago. Visitors can also see a firecracker house next to the shrine where people often throw burning firecrackers during celebrations.
name: San Chao Jui Tui
address: 283 Soi Phutorn, Talat Nuea, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Café Del Mar Phuket, located on Kamala Beach, offers a sophisticated and classy atmosphere for beach club enthusiasts. Despite being an unexpected location for the famous Ibiza nightlife brand, it has become a popular destination since its establishment in 2017. The choice of Kamala Beach over busier areas like Patong Beach provides a more relaxed ambiance while still attracting music lovers from across Phuket.
name: Café Del Mar Phuket
address: 118, 19, Kamala, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Paradise Beach, located on the southwestern coast of Phuket near Patong Bay, offers a unique beachfront nightlife experience with parties celebrating the lunar cycle similar to Koh Phangan's Full Moon Party. The beach retains its natural beauty with clear water and white sand flanked by granite rocks. Surrounded by palm trees and turquoise waters, it is an idyllic destination known for its pristine coastline, vibrant coral reef for snorkeling, and dense rainforest for hiking adventures.
name: Paradise Beach
address: Muen-Ngern Rd, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Small arena staging Muay Thai boxing bouts, with a training gym & a shop selling boxing gear.
detail_description: Patong Boxing Stadium Sainamyen is a small arena in Patong Beach that hosts Muay Thai boxing matches every Wednesday, Friday, and Sunday. The stadium offers an excellent experience for those interested in watching real boxing fights. It features high-level fighters, making it a great place for advanced individuals seeking good sparring opportunities. Additionally, there is a training gym and a shop selling boxing gear on-site.
name: Patong Boxing Stadium Sainamyen
address: 2, 59 Sainamyen Rd, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Spacious animal park with many colorful species of birds in a lush setting with regular bird shows.
detail_description: Nestled in a lush setting, Phuket Bird Park is a spacious animal park showcasing a wide variety of colorful bird species. Visitors can enjoy regular bird shows and close-up encounters with the local avian population. Covering 12 acres of gardens and habitats, the park is home to over 100 different bird variations, offering an immersive experience in the world of birds.
name: Phuket Bird Park
address: 6/2 Chao Fah Tawan Tok Rd, Wichit, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Jungle Xtrem Adventure And Zipline Park, also known as Phuket Tree Adventure, is a thrilling destination located in a rubber plantation above Wat Chalong. The 19,200-square-meter park offers various activities such as tightropes, flying fox, net walking, and different types of bridges. Safety is a top priority here with each participant being equipped with safety harnesses and other gear before embarking on the adventure.
name: Jungle Xtrem Adventure And Zipline Park
address: 54, 17, Chalong, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Step into a world of optical illusions and mind-bending art at the AR Trick Eye Museum Phuket. This museum features themed rooms such as the aqua zone, jungle, art masterpieces, and more, where visitors can interact with 3D paintings that create stunning optical illusions. Located in Phuket Town, this two-story building showcases about 100 painted and sculpted scenes using trompe-l'oeil techniques.
name: Trick Eye Museum Phuket
address: 199 Moo4 T.Wichit, A, Mueang Phuket District, 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Expansive rainforest adventure park featuring treetop walkways & zip lines.
detail_description: Hanuman World is a thrilling rainforest adventure park in Phuket, Thailand, offering treetop walkways and exhilarating zip lines. The 800-meter zipline ride provides an adrenaline-pumping experience as it twists through the dense canopy at high speeds. Visitors can embark on a ziplining journey across 32 platforms in the treetops, enjoying the support of friendly staff.
name: Hanuman World
address: 105 หมู่ที่ 4 ถนนเหมืองเจ้าฟ้า, Wichit, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Kamala, a renowned town and resort destination situated on the western coast of Phuket, is celebrated for its stunning expansive sandy beach and crystal-clear azure waters. This area exudes a serene and laid-back ambiance that appeals to families and couples seeking tranquility. Kamala Beach, with its broad stretch of sand, offers ample space for visitors to find a peaceful spot, even during peak times.
name: Kamala
address: Kathu District, Phuket, Thailand

detail_description: Patong Beach Bangla Walking Street, also known as Soi Bangla or Bangla Road, is the vibrant heart of Phuket Nightlife. The area is filled with bars and discos where visitors can enjoy drinks and play bar games. For those looking for a different experience, nearby night markets offer discounted shopping of souvenirs and local items along with a chance to indulge in Thai cuisine under the starry sky.
name: Patong Beach Bangla Walking Street
address: V7VW+J48, Bangla Rd, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Ketho Dimsum is a popular restaurant in Phuket, offering a variety of Thai breakfast options and specializing in dim sum, which are small portions of food served in steamer baskets. The restaurant provides an affordable dining experience with prices around 150 baht per meal. Customers can expect efficient service and fresh dim sum made to order. The atmosphere is described as kind and unstuffy, attracting both locals and tourists alike.
name: Ketho Dimsum
address: 48, 2 Vichitsongkram Rd, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Low-key white-sand beach in a tranquil setting offering snorkel & umbrella rentals, plus dining.
detail_description: Freedom Beach, located in the lively Patong district, offers a serene and unspoiled setting. Accessible by boat or through an adventurous jungle trek, this 300m strip of white sand provides a peaceful escape from the crowds. With clear turquoise waters and lush greenery as its backdrop, it's an ideal spot for relaxation. Unlike other beaches on the island, Freedom Beach is free from noisy water activities like jet skiing and parasailing.
name: Freedom Beach
address: ถนนศิริราช, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

excerpt: Secluded & relaxed sandy beach overlooked by rustic, open-air restaurants.
detail_description: Tri Trang Beach is a hidden gem in Patong, Phuket, offering a serene and secluded atmosphere for those seeking to escape the hustle and bustle of city life. With its white sandy shores and clear waters, it's an ideal spot for nature lovers and peace-seekers. The 500-meter long beach provides ample space for sunbathing and relaxation.
name: Tri Trang Beach
address: Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Bustling night market with stalls selling clothes, household goods, souvenirs & street food.
detail_description: Malin Plaza is a bustling night market located in lively Patong, offering a wide variety of goods and street food. It's well-known for its beachwear, Thai spa products, and traditional handicrafts. The market provides a cooler shopping environment compared to other busy markets in the area. Visitors can explore tabletop stalls, re-purposed shipping containers, and more under a metal roof.
name: Malin Plaza
address: 162, 51-52 Prachanukhro Rd, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Bustling local market lined with stalls featuring souvenirs, clothing, traditional food & more.
detail_description: Patong Otop Shopping Paradise is a bustling local market in Phuket, Thailand, offering a wide array of souvenirs, clothing, traditional food and more. This night market provides an ideal opportunity to experience the essence of Phuket through discounted shopping and indulging in local cuisine under the starry sky. The concept of OTOP (One Tambon, One Product) showcases products from different villages including food, cloth, silk, handicrafts and more.
name: OTOP Market
address: OTOP Shopping Paradises 237/15-20 Patong BeachRat, Uthit, ถนน 200, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Down-to-earth rooms & suites in a buzzy beachfront hotel with a beach club, a restaurant & a pool.
detail_description: KUDO Hotel & Beach Club is a vibrant and stylish destination located on Bang Tao Beach in Phuket. By day, guests can enjoy relaxing seaside lounging with panoramic sea views from the pool level, while at night, the club comes alive with glamorous parties featuring live music and DJ performances. With its immediate access to Bangla Road, it's an ideal choice for those seeking a high-energy atmosphere by the sea and convenient proximity to nightlife hotspots.
name: KUDO Hotel & Beach Club
address: 33, 1 Patong Beach Shortcut Road, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Chang Wat Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: The Phuket Snake Show is currently undergoing renovations and does not have ongoing shows, but visitors can still interact with the crocodiles by feeding them chicken and taking photos for a fee. The park has been impacted by COVID-19 restrictions, leading to an abandoned atmosphere. Despite this, visitors have found it to be a unique experience and are glad they took the chance to visit.
name: Phuket Snake Show
address: 1/95 moo 5, Chalong, Muang, Phuket, 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Tsunami Memorial Park, located in Khao Lak, serves as a poignant reminder of the devastating 2004 Indian Ocean tsunami. The park features a large bronze circular statue and provides a serene and green space for visitors to pay their respects to the victims of the tragedy. It is a peaceful spot where locals often gather to remember loved ones or reflect on the impact of the disaster.
name: Tsunami Memorial Park
address: 75/2 Na Hat Road, Kamala, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

excerpt: Large wakeboarding park with obstacle courses & lessons, plus other recreational activities.
detail_description: Phuket Wake Park is a sports complex that offers accommodation and other recreational activities. It includes an outdoor swimming pool, fitness center, and bar.
name: Phuket Wake Park
address: 86 Vichitsongkram Rd, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

detail_description: Carnival Magic is a new and exciting Thai carnival theme park, known as the Magical Kingdom of Lights. It boasts numerous record-breaking attractions and features over 40 million lights in its illumination park. The River Palace, an enormous indoor parade show theatre, can accommodate over 2,200 spectators. Conceived by the same organization behind Phuket FantaSea, it was set to open in early 2020 but faced delays due to Covid-19.
name: Carnival Magic
address: 999, Kamala, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

excerpt: Museum showcasing history of Phuket's mining & minerals industry in an airy, colonial-style villa.
detail_description: The Phuket Mining Museum showcases the history of the mining and minerals industry on the island of Phuket. It's located in a colonial-style villa, and is quiet and out of the way but still has some nice grounds to walk around. The museum is well-done, with good exhibits on mining techniques and equipment from days gone by.
name: Phuket Mining Museum
address: W8MX+8QQ, Kathu, Kathu District, Phuket 83120, Thailand

detail_description: Phuket Elephant Care Kathu is a remarkable sanctuary that provides a spacious and enriching environment for elephants, allowing visitors to engage in various activities with these majestic creatures. The friendly and knowledgeable staff, including individuals like Nick, Matt, and Dom, ensure an unforgettable experience by offering opportunities such as feeding the elephants, mud baths, and bathing sessions without riding them. Additionally, guests can enjoy authentic Thai cuisine and even learn how to cook it while being immersed in the fascinating history of elephants.
name: Phuket Elephant Care Kathu
